explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to count the number of ways to express n as the sum of the xth power of unique positive integers. The main function iterates over all possible values of i and recursively calls the countWays function to count the number of ways to express n - i^x as the sum of the xth power of unique positive integers. The countWays function uses memoization to avoid redundant calculations.

